*** Ibis 1.3 ***

general:
- keep a changelog, publish it on the website
- update documentation
- copy the source of "util" and "connect" to the distro manually
- make sure all source files have a cvs id.
- try it on windows 2000, windows XP, cygwin, MacOS.

nameserver:
- lookup of ibisses that died/left/mustleave is sequential now. Could become
  bottleneck.
	
ipl:
+ add calls to IPL: amount of data written/read in a message so far.
  this is needed for traffic shaping (Done Ceriel)
- make oneToMany+manyToOne illegal in port types. May cause deadlocks because
  of lack of flow-control in multicasts. Current users: tuplespace and
  globalresulttable in Satin.
+ add a sendport.disconnect(timeout) and sendport.close(timeout) if needed.
  (I don't think this is needed: you need a timeout at the receiver side
   because it waits for the senders to close (Ceriel)).

satin:  
- check Satin Shared Objects for (performance) bugs
- detection of what is an inlet: now, if the invocation is inside a try-catch
  it is assumed to be an inlet. Is this OK?
+ abort bug: throw an Exception instead of returning null. Sequential user
  code gets confused otherwise. Done (Ceriel)

connect:
- Update manual and readme files to reflect new structure.

apps:
+ check satin barnes performance drop since Gosia's paper

implementations:
+ TcpIbis: handle IOException thrown in upcall _after_ 
  finish of message properly (Done Ceriel)
+ TcpIbis: always print errors in ConnectionHandler, not only if debug is
  enabled (Done Ceriel)

